Subject: Re: [VB] Carb Ice-ing

 do a complete tunbeup including points, timing, adjust valves, etc.
 
the idle problem may be elsewhere.
 
icing is normal during damp cool weather.  to stop it, install a stock air cleaner AND paper pre-heat tube.  the paper tube sould go down through the rear engijne tin, onto the metal pre heat that attaches under a muffler to head nut.  
 
 The pre heat tube is crucial to compleat de-icing, a heat riser cannot do it alone.  The riser does the horizontal part of the manifold, but not the throat or the carb.
 
yes the 30 pict 1 is interchangable, and imo is a better carb.
oh, does the 30 pict 2 have 2 screws?
 
